00:00:30.950 --> 00:00:33.440 align:middle line:84%
Many of us have heard
that poor posture

00:00:33.440 --> 00:00:36.380 align:middle line:84%
is related to things like
chronic pain, headaches,

00:00:36.380 --> 00:00:37.640 align:middle line:90%
and fatigue.

00:00:37.640 --> 00:00:40.370 align:middle line:84%
In the past, fitness
culture has taught us

00:00:40.370 --> 00:00:43.610 align:middle line:84%
that regular exercise and
stretching is a key component

00:00:43.610 --> 00:00:44.930 align:middle line:90%
to good posture.

00:00:44.930 --> 00:00:46.970 align:middle line:84%
But what does good
posture really mean?

00:00:46.970 --> 00:00:51.260 align:middle line:84%
And how do we attain and
sustain such a state?

00:00:51.260 --> 00:00:54.350 align:middle line:84%
Modern scientific discoveries
in the fields of anatomy,

00:00:54.350 --> 00:00:57.790 align:middle line:84%
and biomechanics, and movement
disciplines-- like yoga,

00:00:57.790 --> 00:00:59.540 align:middle line:90%
Pilates and Tai chi--

00:00:59.540 --> 00:01:02.960 align:middle line:84%
reveal that posture is not
simply a physical concept.

00:01:02.960 --> 00:01:06.470 align:middle line:84%
But rather, part of a much
broader and much more intricate

00:01:06.470 --> 00:01:10.550 align:middle line:84%
combination of things going
on between our body and mind.

00:01:10.550 --> 00:01:13.140 align:middle line:84%
Today, I'm here
with Ben Stewart--

00:01:13.140 --> 00:01:16.780 align:middle line:84%
film maker and musician,
turned movement specialist.

00:01:16.780 --> 00:01:20.480 align:middle line:84%
Ben studies the science and art
of natural movement and body

00:01:20.480 --> 00:01:23.930 align:middle line:84%
communication as a pathway
to awakening to our highest

00:01:23.930 --> 00:01:25.920 align:middle line:90%
human potential.

00:01:25.920 --> 00:01:27.930 align:middle line:84%
Ben, thank you for
being here today.

00:01:27.930 --> 00:01:29.888 align:middle line:84%
>> Thank you so much for
